  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2009-01-06",
    "date": "2009-01-15T21:09:22Z",
    "text": "Bad Polluters Act of 2009- Amends the Internal Revenue Code to deny to a Great Lakes polluter the taxpayer election to expense 50% of the cost of refinery property in the current taxpayer year. Defines \"Great Lakes polluter\" as a refinery owner that holds a permit issued by the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) to discharge a certain level of pollutants into the Great Lakes."
